SIMPLE: aigrette
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aigrette
<hw>Ai*grette</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., a sort of white heron,
with a tuft of feathers on its head; a tuft of feathers; dim. of the
same word as <ets>heron</ets>. See <er>Heron</er>, and cf.
<er>Egret</er>, <er>Egrette</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The small white European heron. See <er>Egret</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plume or tuft for the head composed of feathers,
or of gems, etc.</def> <rj><au>Prescott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A tuft like that of the egret.</def>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A feathery crown of seed; egret; <as>as, the
<ex>aigrette</ex> or down of the dandelion or the
thistle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aiguille</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
